#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:1
msgid "ANARI Rendering Module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:3
msgid ""
"You can now use [ANARI](https://www.khronos.org/anari), by enabling the "
"`vtkRenderingANARI` module, for rendering. At least one [ANARI](https://www."
"khronos.org/anari) back-end needs to be in your `LIBRARY_PATH` and the "
"`ANARI_LIBRARY` environment variable needs to be set with the correct back-"
"end name (e.g. `export ANARI_LIBRARY=visrtx`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:5
msgid ""
"Any back-end compatible with **ANARI-SDK version 0.9.1** will work. [NVIDIA "
"VisRTX](https://github.com/NVIDIA/VisRTX) version 0.7.1 has been tested and "
"is compatible with this release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:7
msgid "Here's the list of other publicly available back-ends:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:9
msgid ""
"[AMD RadeonProRender](https://github.com/GPUOpen-LibrariesAndSDKs/"
"RadeonProRenderANARI)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:10
msgid "[Intel OSPRay](https://github.com/ospray/anari-ospray)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:11
msgid "[NVIDIA USD](https://github.com/NVIDIA-Omniverse/AnariUsdDevice)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-anari-rendering-capability.md:13
msgid ""
"⚠️ Before using any back-end, check that the version is compatible with "
"**ANARI-SDK version 0.9.1**."
msgstr ""
